  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "There are legal requirements for reporting suspicious financial activities that may indicate money laundering, particularly for financial institutions and certain businesses. Specific reporting obligations vary by jurisdiction but generally include:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting to financial intelligence units\n2. Submitting suspicious activity reports (SARs)\n3. Verifying customer identities\n4. Maintaining transaction records\n5. Implementing anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n\nThese requirements aim to help prevent financial crimes.",
